DOCUMENT();
loadMacros('PGstandard.pl', 'PGML.pl', 'PGcourse.pl');

$x   = random(5, 9);
$xsq = $x**2;

BEGIN_PGML
A square garden has [$xsq] square feet.  So the perimeter of the garden must be
[_]{Real(4*$x)} feet

END_PGML

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
Since the garden is square,each side must be [`\sqrt{[$xsq]}=[$x]`] feet.

The perimeter is the sum of the lengths of the four [$x] foot sides so it is [@ 4*$x @] feet.
END_PGML_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();

